Unfortunately I can only give the same answer as in previous BigQueryIO refactorings: it's most likely not update-safe, but there also most likely is no way to get where we want to be while keeping it update-safe, and I'm suggesting to ignore this issue because we don't have a general approach to making any but trivial changes update-safe, nor a strict requirement to do that.

We should think about this then. This transform is largely used by Dataflow
users, many of whom do rely on update. It is also probably the most common
sink used by streaming Dataflow users, so we risk making the majority of
pipelines not updatable. The previous time I believe we were able to limit
the scope sufficiently.
